The paper discusses a biologically motivated model based on neural networks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses a learning framework for the proposed model, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper uses stochastic synapses and variational learning, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. Finally, the paper applies the proposed model to structured output prediction and semi-supervised learning tasks, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
